---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="TRACKID — The Story" description="The TRACKID story: how a Beijing roast duck sticker inspired by the Columbus dove became a global track bike icon. Steel frames, fixed gears, no shortcuts." ogType="article">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">The Story</span>
      <h1 class="display" style="font-size: 48px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 4px; margin-top: 16px; line-height: 1.1;">
        A Duck That<br />Won't Stay Put
      </h1>
    </div>

    <div class="story-body">
      <p>Every steel frame rider knows the Columbus dove — that little white bird that says your tubes are the real deal. <span class="notranslate">TRACKID</span>'s Roast Duck sticker is our nod to that icon, swapping the Italian dove for a Beijing roast duck. Same oval. Same reverence. Way better flavor.</p>
      <p>But the sticker is more than a design gag. It's <span class="notranslate">TRACKID</span> in one image.</p>
      <p>Beijing roast duck is the city's defining dish — carved tableside, served on proper plates, the kind of thing that represents centuries of craft and culture. The track bike is our thing — steel frames, fixed gears, no shortcuts. One belongs to Beijing's culinary heritage, the other to its street riding scene. They shouldn't go together, but somehow they do. That tension is <span class="notranslate">TRACKID</span>: taking something iconic and serious, and putting it on two wheels where it doesn't belong.</p>
      <p>We listed the sticker on AliExpress for the price of a cheap beer. No ads. No influencer drops. Just a duck on a bike, sitting between phone cases and LED strips. Then something happened.</p>
      <p>A kid in London stuck it on a Vigorelli. A messenger in São Paulo slapped it on a beater Pista. Someone in Tokyo put it on a NJS frame worth more than our rent. A dude in Melbourne stuck it on his helmet, ruining a perfectly clean aesthetic. On purpose.</p>
      <p>More and more orders across dozens of countries. Zero marketing budget. One very well-traveled duck.</p>
      <p>This page is the proof. Every photo, every city, every rider who looked at this duck and thought: <em>yeah, that's mine.</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">The Sticker</span>
      <h2 class="display" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 3px; margin-top: 16px; line-height: 1.1;">
        Peking Duck<br />Hot Duck
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="sticker-showcase">
      <img src="/pekingduck-sticker.jpg" alt="TRACKID Peking Duck sticker — Columbus-style oval with a roast duck, next to the HOT DUCK spec sheet" class="sticker-img" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-bottom: 80px;">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">Contact</span>
      <h2 class="display" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 3px; margin-top: 16px; line-height: 1.1;">
        Get In Touch
      </h2>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted);">
      Questions, collabs, or just want to talk bikes and ducks?
    </p>
    <a href="mailto:trackid_bj@126.com" class="contact-email">trackid_bj@126.com</a>

    <div class="social-links">
      <a href="https://www.instagram.com/trackid_beijing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="social-icon" aria-label="Instagram">
        <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <rect x="2" y="2" width="20" height="20" rx="5" />
          <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="5" />
          <circle cx="17.5" cy="6.5" r="1" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" />
        </svg>
      </a>
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@TRACKID-Beijing" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="social-icon" aria-label="YouTube">
        <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M22.54 6.42a2.78 2.78 0 0 0-1.94-2C18.88 4 12 4 12 4s-6.88 0-8.6.46a2.78 2.78 0 0 0-1.94 2A29 29 0 0 0 1 12a29 29 0 0 0 .46 5.58 2.78 2.78 0 0 0 1.94 2C5.12 20 12 20 12 20s6.88 0 8.6-.46a2.78 2.78 0 0 0 1.94-2A29 29 0 0 0 23 12a29 29 0 0 0-.46-5.58z" />
          <polygon points="9.75 15.02 15.5 12 9.75 8.98 9.75 15.02" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" />
        </svg>
      </a>
      <a href="https://www.xiaohongshu.com/user/profile/5b474eb7e8ac2b3455d564a4" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="social-icon" aria-label="Xiaohongshu">
        <img src="/xiaohongshu.jpg" alt="Xiaohongshu" class="social-img" width="22" height="22" />
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .story-body {
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .story-body p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .story-body em {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .sticker-showcase {
    max-width: 420px;
    margin-top: 24px;
  }

  .sticker-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
  }

  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .sticker-showcase {
    background: #f0ece6;
    padding: 16px;
  }

  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .sticker-img {
    mix-blend-mode: normal;
  }

  .contact-email {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 16px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--signal-red);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--signal-red);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
  }

  .contact-email:hover {
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .social-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }

  .social-icon {
    color: var(--muted);
    transition: color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .social-icon:hover {
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .social-img {
    display: block;
    border-radius: 4px;
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
    opacity: 0.55;
    transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
  }

  .social-icon:hover .social-img {
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .social-img {
    filter: invert(1);
    mix-blend-mode: lighten;
  }
</style>
